<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-17T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-17T05:00:00-05:00" n="221" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1121 Osborn, L. C./2: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-17T18:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">May 17,
                                        1928—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>362. My 266 April 25, 10 a.m. Osborn has telegraphed his wife from
                            Kaifengfu that he is “with Ashcraft.”<note n="13" xml:id="d221fn13">Rev.
                                E. P. Asheraft, superintendent of the American Free Methodist
                                Mission, Jungtseh, Honan.</note> It is presumed therefore that he is
                            released and safe.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>